What can you do with AT&T Office@Hand?

Every AT&T Office@Hand plan empowers your team.

Unified communications and collaboration

Manage audio, video, SMS, file sharing, chat, and whiteboarding on a single, AI-powered platformsynced across desk phones, smartphones, and desktops.

Advanced contact center features

Go next level with call monitoring for managers, call parking, automated call recording, Interactive Voice Response (IVR), and communications analytics.

AI assistance

Say goodbye to missed calls with AI Receptionist enhanced features like call transcription, CRM updates, and real-time coaching.

300+ integrations with essential business apps

Keep business communications seamless with native integrations for apps like Google Workspace, Microsoft 365, Box, Dropbox, and more.

AT&T Office@Hand with Contact Center

Handle all communications in one AI-enhanced platform

Help reps manage customers on one platform, with features like:
 

  • Voice, text, and video across 20+ digital channels
  • AI-enhanced agents for tips and help during calls
  • Transcriptions and summaries of calls
  • Integration with leading CRMs like Salesforce and Zendesk

RingSense for AT&T Office@Hand

Make every call count with our dedicated AI-enhanced assistant

RingSense helps your agents get more out of every call, with powerful AI features like:
 

  • Transcription, summarization, key takeaways, and action items from each call
  • Call insights, including keyword, objection, and competitor mentions
  • Filterable reports to help managers find common agent or customer issues
  • AI-powered coaching to help all agents improve and save managers time

Why do businesses
choose AT&T Office@Hand?

We know modern business communications can be tough. Thats why weve combined everything into one simple, scalable solution.

Delighted customers

With just one number across all your devices, customers can easily connect to the right person with a much smoother experience

More flexible work

Keep teams productive with the devices they already have and prefer, like smartphones, tablets, softphones, or desktop IP phones.

Maximized time and budget

Skip the lengthy setup, dev teams, and hardware maintenance of old phone systemsget up and running right away.

Simpler, unified experience

Spend more time serving customers instead of juggling apps and data, thanks to the all-in-one web-based service.

Your UCaaS equipment arrives pre-configured so all you have to do is plug it in. Complimentary white glove service is provided in the form of 3 one-hour phone sessions to acclimate the administrator to the portal and administration of the service.

We strongly recommend ordering new equipment from AT&T to help ensure a smooth implementation, but if you have Office@Hand-compatible equipment, instructions are provided for how to configure that equipment. Caveat: AT&T will not be able to provide help desk support for non-AT&T purchased equipment.

AT&T Office@Hand is an over-the-top UCaaS service that will work with any internet service.

You can find out more about our UCaaS solution 24/7: Learn more about AT&T Office@Hand features and self-help options on the ASECare Portal.

Office@Hand apps can be downloaded from the ASECare Portal. Our UCaaS apps are compatible with Windows, Mac, iOS, and Android
